<subSubSection id="0FD275692FE8D0A18AD8F92DB14FA46C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="238F76753DE7D31966250ACB4606C31F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E1E9C43F44187656C4A657F359EC9AA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
3.0-3.1 mm long (mean = 3.03 mm; n = 3); 2.5-2.82
<normalizedToken id="9C6A7832E2D4B27EE9AC62AEFC80E34F" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by its large size; elytral disc broadly and deeply transversely impressed with a saddle-like depression from scutellum to declivital base; declivity deeply sulcate, its margins lined by large tubercles on interstriae 1 and 3-6; elytral base emarginated from sutural margin to interstriae 4 to accommodate mycangial tuft, mycangial tuft setae long, very dense; and posterolateral costa absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
